text.section:
An individual may apply to become a registered voter:
at a local board office or the State Board office;
at a registration site administered by a local board;
by mail;
when applying to the Motor Vehicle Administration for the issuance, renewal, or modification of a driver's license or identification card;
when applying for services at a voter registration agency;
through the State Board's online voter registration system; or
with the assistance of a volunteer authorized by the State or local board.
